</blockquote>
<p>That one I grant you. About the ONLY reason MIGHT be the composition and/or size. Car batteries have been rechargeable for the longest time, and the entire structure of the inside of the phone would point to &quot;Hey, you stick something in this end with power and it recharges!&quot; They would actually be more shocked by the concept that it was a radio capable of transmission and reception <em>simultaneously</em> while still being incredibley tiny - and that they would be so cheap a kid would have one! (Now you know why the Foundation has so many resources! &quot;Buy into American Telephone and Telegraph!&quot;)</p>

